<p>First up is Theremin ‚Äò75, a concert of music for Theremin, iPad and computer in October. This concert was held to recreate a performance by noted Australian media artist Stanislaus Ostoja-Kotkowski at the Australia ‚Äò75 festival in Canberra. Larry Sitsky‚Äôs 1975 work Legions of Asmodeus was performed on one of Ostoja-Kotkowski‚Äôs restored theremins which is part of the ANU Art Collection and three recreations by Alistair Riddell and Stephen Jones.</p>

<p>Here‚Äôs some photos from the rehearsals and performance. The ensemble was Christina Hopgood, Yvonne Lam, Jonathan Griffiths and me!</p>

