<p>It was a bit tricky getting the four instruments up and running, theremins typically have small aerials while these instruments had quite large pieces of steel! As a result, our bodies were always in the electric field of the theremin so we had to tune the instruments while on stage. Given that the instruments were on display in a gallery we weren‚Äôt able to look at each other so we used <a href="http://decibel.waapamusic.com/decibelscoreplayer/">Decibel‚Äôs ScorePlayer iPad app</a> to synchronise a scrolling score to perform the work cohesively. The result was loud, crazy, and a lot of fun! Here‚Äôs the video:</p>

